    string

typeAlias SecuritySubType_t: <"Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType. As an example for SecurityType(167)=\"REPO\", the SecuritySubType=\"General Collateral\" can be used to further specify the type of REPO.  If SecuritySubType is used, then SecurityType is required.  For SecurityType=\"MLEG\" a name of the option or futures strategy name can be specified, such as \"Calendar\", \"Vertical\", \"Butterfly\".  For SecurityType(167)=\"OPT\" the subclassification can be specified, such as \"Asian\".  For SecurityType(167)=\"SWAPTION\" a value of \"Straddle\" is used to identify a straddle swaption.  In the context of EU SFTR reporting use the appropriate 4-character code noted in the regulations - \"GENE\" for general collateral or \"SPEC\" for specific collateral (without quote marks).">
    string

